{
  "texts": [
    "MitigationsAI supply chain attacks can be mitigated by supply chain assurance practices.",
    "For model fle dependencies, this includes regular vulnerability scanning of the model artifacts used in the ML pipeline [292], and by adopting safe model persistence formats like safetensors.For webscale data dependencies, this includes verifying web downloads by publishing (by the provider) cryptographic hashes and verifying (by the downloader) training data as a basic integrity check to ensure that domain hijacking has not injected new sources of data into the training dataset [46].",
    "Another approach to mitigating risks associated with malicious image editing by large diffusion models is immunizing images to make them resistant to manipulation by these models [254].",
    "However, this approach requires an additional policy component to make it effective and practical.",
    "Direct Prompt Injection Attacks and MitigationsA direct prompt injection occurs when a user injects text that is intended to alter the behavior of the LLM.Attacker goals."
  ]
}